(LEAD) At least seven killed, 20 injured in bus terminal fire
GOYANG, South Korea, May 26 (Yonhap) -- At least seven people were killed and 20 others injured in a fire at a local bus terminal on Monday, firefighters and hospital officials said.
The blaze occurred about 9:10 a.m. at an underground construction site of the Goyang Bus Terminal in Goyang, just northwest of Seoul, firefighters said. The fire was brought under control in about 20 minutes.